<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gown" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gown,</orth> any long loose upper garment; 1) worn by women: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 72</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 72</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 15</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.844" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 844</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 62</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 62</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.172" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 74</bibl>.<lb />2) worn by men: <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 226</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 226</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.6.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 6, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.6.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 6, 120</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 83</bibl> <cit><quote>a furred g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 169</bibl>. <cit><quote>an almsman's g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.149" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>black mourning --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 161</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wear the surplice of humility over the black g. of a big heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.99" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 99</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>one that hath two --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 88</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) the dress of a civil magistrate or a divine: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 111</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 44</bibl>. 93 (the Roman toga).
<lb />4) a dressing gown to make one's self easy: <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.197" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 231</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 231</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 231</bibl>
